OL,7,F"His mother woke him up in the morning
OL,8,Fto give him the dreadful news after
OL,9,Fshe heard it on the radio. So many of
OL,10,Fhis lifelong friends and workmates
OL,11,Fwere killed, it's impossible to
OL,12,Fimagine how devastated he felt.
OL,14,F"Our father often told us the story of
OL,15,Fthe disaster as my sister Lynne and I
OL,16,Fgrew up. He told us he was the
OL,17,Fluckiest man to be alive."
